videos.headline: Texas strikes first in Ames
videos.description: Longhorns RB Chris Warren III rushes up the middle 11 yards for the score as Texas jumps out to a 7-0 lead against Iowa State.

videos.headline: Texas' trick play turns into fumble
videos.description: Trying to get creative with a reverse, the Longhorns cough up the football when the Cyclones defense tackled RB Chris Warren III before the second handoff, which forced an awkward pitch and fumble.

videos.headline: Park pressured and throws INT
videos.description: Texas DB DeShon Elliott catches his third interception in two games on a Jacob Park rollout throw into traffic in the second quarter.

videos.headline: Buechele stands tall in pocket, throws TD strike
videos.description: Longhorns QB Shane Buechele gets hit hard in the pocket while zinging  a 22-yard score to freshman Toneil Carter behind the Iowa State defense to give Texas a 14-0 lead in the second quarter.

videos.headline: Second Park INT kills Iowa St. drive
videos.description: The Cyclones were looking to put points on the board before halftime, but Texas DB Kris Boyd intercepts the Jacob Park floater. Park is 1-for-11 with two picks on throws over 10 yards tonight.

videos.headline: Texas' Herman making adjustments against different Cyclones defense
videos.description: Coach Tom Herman says QB Shane Buechele is playing "tough" against an Iowa State defense that is playing different than what the Longhorns practiced for in the first half.

videos.headline: Murdock snags catch sitting down
videos.description: Iowa State's Marchie Murdock slips on his route but makes the catch on the ground for the first down as the Cyclones try to get some momentum going against the Longhorns at the start of the second half.

videos.headline: Buechele scrambles and converts long third down
videos.description: Texas QB Shane Buechele gives himself some time by spinning out of a sack and connects with Collin Johnson 25 yards downfield to convert a third-and-17 against Cyclones.

videos.headline: Texas' drive ends on Buechele INT
videos.description: Longhorns QB Shane Buechele is pressured by the Cyclones' front and throws an interception over the middle of the field to Kamari Cotton-Moya giving Iowa State the ball with good field position as they look for their first points in the third quarter.

videos.headline: Cyclones back in game with TD
videos.description: QB Jacob Park stands patiently in the pocket and steps up to find Matthew Eaton in the end zone to make game 14-7 in the third quarter against Texas.

videos.headline: Coach and QB show emotion on sideline prior to TD
videos.description: Iowa State coach Matt Campbell and QB Jacob Park share words in an emotional exchange just before Park threw his first touchdown of the night.

videos.headline: Elliott grabs second pick
videos.description: Texas' DeShon Elliott intercepts Jacob Park's overthrow intended for Hakeem Butler for the second time tonight at the end of the third quarter as the Longhorns protect a 14-7 lead.
